[32m+[m[32m# Agent Instructions[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m> This file is mirrored across CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and GEMINI.md so the same instructions load in any AI environment.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mYou operate within a 3-layer architecture that separates concerns to maximize reliability. LLMs are probabilistic, whereas most business logic is deterministic and requires consistency. This system fixes that mismatch.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## The 3-Layer Architecture[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Layer 1: Directive (What to do)**[m
[32m+[m[32m- Basically just SOPs written in Markdown, live in `directives/`[m
[32m+[m[32m- Define the goals, inputs, tools/scripts to use, outputs, and edge cases[m
[32m+[m[32m- Natural language instructions, like you'd give a mid-level employee[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Layer 2: Orchestration (Decision making)**[m
[32m+[m[32m- This is you. Your job: intelligent routing.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Read directives, call execution tools in the right order, handle errors, ask for clarification, update directives with learnings[m
[32m+[m[32m- You're the glue between intent and execution.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Layer 3: Execution (Doing the work)**[m
[32m+[m[32m- Deterministic Python scripts in `execution/`[m
[32m+[m[32m- Environment variables, api tokens, etc are stored in `.env`[m
[32m+[m[32m- Handle API calls, data processing, file operations, database interactions[m
[32m+[m[32m- Reliable, testable, fast. Use scripts instead of manual work. Commented well.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Operating Principles[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**1. Check for tools first**[m
[32m+[m[32mBefore writing a script, check `execution/` per your directive. Only create new scripts if none exist.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**2. Self-anneal when things break**[m
[32m+[m[32m- Read error message and stack trace[m
[32m+[m[32m- Fix the script and test it again (unless it uses paid tokens/credits/etc)[m
[32m+[m[32m- Update the directive with what you learned[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**3. Update directives as you learn**[m
[32m+[m[32mDirectives are living documents. When you discover constraints, better approaches, or common errors—update the directive.[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## Self-annealing loop[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32mErrors are learning opportunities. When something breaks:[m
[32m+[m[32m1. Fix it[m
[32m+[m[32m2. Update the tool[m
[32m+[m[32m3. Test tool, make sure it works[m
[32m+[m[32m4. Update directive to include new flow[m
[32m+[m[32m5. System is now stronger[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m## File Organization[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- `.tmp/` - All intermediate files. Never commit, always regenerated.[m
[32m+[m[32m- `execution/` - Python scripts (the deterministic tools)[m
[32m+[m[32m- `directives/` - SOPs in Markdown (the instruction set)[m
[32m+[m[32m- `.env` - Environment variables and API keys[m
[32m+[m[32m- `credentials.json`, `token.json` - Google OAuth credentials[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m**Key principle:** Local files are only for processing. Deliverables live in cloud services.[m
